briefdescription.para: The file name of the atmosphere table.

detaileddescription.para: The file name of the atmosphere table. The file should contain four columns of data, containing altitude (first column), and the associated density, pressure and density values in the second, third and fourth columns.

briefdescription.para: A vector of strings containing the names of the independent variables contained in the atmosphere file.

detaileddescription.para: A vector of strings containing the names of the independent variables contained in the atmosphere file, in the correct order (from left, being the first entry in the vector, to the right).

briefdescription.para: Vector containing the independent variables.

Vector of integers that specifies the order of dentity, pressure, temperature, gas constant and ratio of specific heats are located.

briefdescription.para: Specific gas constant of the atmosphere.

Interpolation for pressure. Note that type of interpolator depends on number of independent variables specified.

Behavior of interpolator when independent variable is outside range.
Default values to be used for extrapolation.

detaileddescription.para:
Default values to be used for extrapolation. The structure of the vector is as follows:
outer vector: one element for each dependent variable (density, pressure, temperature, ect.)
inner vector: one element for each independent variable (latitude, longitude and altitude)
pair: first element in case independent variable is below its lower definition limit, second element in case it is above the upper definition limit

briefdescription.para: Default constructor.

detaileddescription.para:
Default constructor.
atmosphereTableFile
Map of files containing information on the atmosphere. The order of both independent and dependent parameters needs to be specified in the independentVariablesNames and dependentVariablesNames vectors, respectively. Note that specific gas constant and specific heat ratio will be given the default constant values for Earth, unless they are included in the file map.
independentVariablesNames
List of independent parameters describing the atmosphere.
dependentVariablesNames
List of dependent parameters output by the atmosphere.
specificGasConstant
The constant specific gas constant of the atmosphere.
ratioOfSpecificHeats
The constant ratio of specific heats of the atmosphere.
boundaryHandling
Method for interpolation behavior when independent variable is out of range.
defaultExtrapolationValue
Default value to be used for extrapolation, in case of use_default_value or use_default_value_with_warning as methods for boundaryHandling.
